<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n28053i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n28" href="#n28053i">N28 (VI.D.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n28all.htm#n28053i"> 53(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> history, latin &amp; piety</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Education in 18th Century]</font> The Rev. James Fontaine was a French minister in this city, and about two hundred years ago he announced that &ldquo;he will board gentlemen&apos;s sons in his house, which he hath taken in Stephen&apos;s Green, and will teach them the French, <mark>Latin</mark> and Greek tongues, also <mark>history</mark>, geography, and mathem,atics, <mark>and especially piety</mark>, for &pound;20 a year and 2 guineas entrance&rdquo;. <small> A. Peter, <a name="APDF1" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#APDF1"><cite title="source">Dublin Fragments, social and historic</cite></a> (1925) 112</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
